  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Superintendent (Oil Tanker)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist the Senior Technical Manager in overseeing the technical operations of a fleet of tankers.</li>\n  <li>Manage daily maintenance and repair activities, budget survey schedules, and docking operations.</li>\n  <li>Maintain updated records of class status and coordinate with Classification Societies, Suppliers, and Contractors for daily operations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure adherence to statutory requirements under ISM, ISPS, and MLC.</li>\n  <li>Monitor, coordinate, and attend vessel inspections by oil majors, statutory surveys, and follow up on related matters.</li>\n  <li>Conduct and report on incident/accident investigations.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Sea-going experience as a Marine Engineer and atleast 2 years of shore experience as technical superintendent.</li>\n  <li>MOT Engineer Certification (Class 1).</li>\n  <li>Strong organizational skills with a hands-on approach to technical troubleshooting and problem-solving.</li>\n  <li>Independent, resourceful, and able to work under pressure to meet deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Willingness and ability to travel on short notice as needed.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 2,
